The area of the triangle is $\frac{1}{2}(8)(10) = 40$ square inches.  Dividing the triangle into 8 equal areas means each piece has area $\frac{40}{8} = 5$ square inches.  We can divide the triangle into four smaller triangles, each with base 4 inches and height 5 inches, so each of these has area $\frac{1}{2}(4)(5) = 10/2 = 5$ square inches.  Thus, we can cut the triangle into eight pieces by cutting each of these triangles in half along its height, as shown below.  [asy]
