The area of the triangle is $\frac{1}{2}(8)(10) = 40$.  We want to cut this into 8 pieces of equal area, so each piece will have area $5$.  Let the triangle be $ABC$, where $AB=AC=8$ and $BC=10$.  Drop an altitude from $A$ to $BC$ and let the intersection point be $D$.  Then $AD=6$ and $BD=DC=2$.  We want to cut the triangle into 8 pieces that have equal area, so we can do this by cutting $AD$ into 8 equal segments, as shown below.  [asy]
