\[BD = \sqrt{13^2 - AD^2}.\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $ACD,$
\[CD = \sqrt{14^2 - AD^2}.\]Since $BD + CD = 15,$
\[\sqrt{13^2 - AD^2} + \sqrt{14^2 - AD^2} = 15.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[13^2 - AD^2 + 2 \sqrt{(13^2 - AD^2)(14^2 - AD^2)} + 14^2 - AD^2 = 15^2.\]Then $2 \sqrt{(13^2 - AD^2)(14^2 - AD^2)} = 2 \cdot 12 \cdot 5,$ so
