\[\frac{r_1^2 + 2 r_1 r_2 + r_2^2}{(r_1 + r_2)^2} = \frac{1}{3}.\]Hence,
\[(O_1 O_2)^2 = \frac{1}{3} AD^2.\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $ABD,$
\[AD^2 = 13^2 - BD^2.\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $CBD,$
\[BD^2 = 15^2 - CD^2.\]Then
\[AD^2 = 13^2 - (15^2 - CD^2) = CD^2 - 56.\]Hence,
\[(O_1 O_2)^2 = \frac{1}{3} (CD^2 - 56).\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $ACD,$
\[CD^2 = 14^2 - AD^2 = 14^2 - (CD^2 - 56),\]so $2CD^2 = 14^2 + 56,$ or $CD^2 = 85.$  Therefore,
\[(O_1 O_2)^2 = \frac{1}{3} (85 - 56) = \frac{29}{3}.\]Thus, $O_1 O_2 = \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{87}}{\sqrt{3}}}.$

