Let $AP = x$ and $AQ = y.$  Then $PB = 12 - x$ and $QC = 17 - y.$

The area of triangle $ABC$ is given by Heron's formula as
\[\sqrt{27 \cdot 10 \cdot 7 \cdot 10} = 2 \cdot 5 \cdot 3 \sqrt{14}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABC,$
\[\cos A = \frac{12^2 + 17^2 - 25^2}{2 \cdot 12 \cdot 17} = \frac{33}{68}.\]Then by the Law of Cosines on triangle $APQ,$
\begin{align*}
PQ^2 &= x^2 + y^2 - 2xy \cos A \\
&= x^2 + y^2 - 2xy \cdot \frac{33}{68}.
\end{align*}By the Law of Cosines on triangle $BPC,$
\begin{align*}
BP^2 &= 144 + x^2 - 24x \cos A, \\
PC^2 &= 289 + y^2 - 34y \cos A.
\end{align*}By the Law of Cosines on triangle $CQR,$
\begin{align*}
CQ^2 &= 289 + y^2 - 34y \cos A, \\
CR^2 &= 625 + (12 - x)^2 - 120 (12 - x) \cos A.
\end{align*}Finally, by the Law of Cosines on triangle $BRS,$
\[BR^2 = 625 + (12 - x)^2 - 120 (12 - x) \cos A.\]Then
\begin{align*}
[PQRS] &= PQ \cdot RS \\
&= PQ \cdot (BR - BC + CQ) \\
&= PQ \cdot \left( \sqrt{625 + (12 - x)^2 - 120 (12 - x) \cos A} - 25 + \sqrt{289 + y^2 - 34y \cos A} \right) \\
&= PQ \cdot \left( \sqrt{625 + (12 - x)^2 - 120 (12 - x) \cdot \frac{33}{68}} - 25 + \sqrt{289 + y^2 - 34y \cdot \frac{33}{68}} \right) \\
&= \sqrt{14} \cdot PQ \cdot \left( \sqrt{(12 - x)^2 - 120 (12 - x) \cdot \frac{33}{68} + 625} + \sqrt{y^2 - 34y \cdot \frac{33}{68} + 289} - 25 \right).
\end{align*}We want to write this in the form $\alpha \omega - \beta \omega^2.$  Note that
\begin{align*}
\sqrt{(12 - x)^2 - 120 (12 - x) \cdot \frac{33}{68} + 625} &= \sqrt{(x - 3)(x - 9)}, \\
\sqrt{y^2 - 34y \cdot \frac{33}{68} + 289} &= \sqrt{\left( y - \frac{17}{2} \right)^2 - \frac{33}{4}}.
\end{align*}Let $z = \omega - \frac{17}{2}.$  Then
\begin{align*}
[PQRS] &= \sqrt{14} \cdot PQ \cdot \left( \sqrt{(x - 3)(x - 9)} + \sqrt{z^2 - \frac{33}{4}} \right) - 25 \sqrt{14} \cdot PQ \\
&= \sqrt{14} \cdot PQ \cdot \left( \sqrt{(x - 3)(x - 9)} + \sqrt{z^2 - \frac{33}{4}} - \frac{25}{\sqrt{14}} \cdot PQ \right) + \frac{25}{2} \cdot 17 \cdot \sqrt{14} \\
&= \sqrt{14} \cdot PQ \cdot \left( \sqrt{(x - 3)(x - 9)} + \sqrt{z^2 - \frac{33}{4}} - \frac{25}{\sqrt{14}} \cdot PQ \right) + \frac{2125}{2}.
\end{align*}Thus, $\beta = \frac{25}{\sqrt{14}},$ and $m + n = \boxed{214}.$

